Title: Geberit FlowFit 620.080.00.1 Equal tee 16mm
Description: Part of a comprehensive system, this Geberit FlowFit 16mm equal tee is made of polyphenylsulfone (PPSU) and fitted with press-fit connections. Developed with the input of the plumbers who will use it, the innovative FlowFit system ensures always-right installation, for a simpler job on-site with no need for deburring and calibration when cutting to length and the ability to laterally press and rotate for convenient and reliable pressing in difficult spots with no risk of contortion. This system is compatible with both cold and hot potable water, cooling and heating water with or without antifreeze agent and with service water and process water. It can also be used in treated water, rainwater with a pH value of <gt/>6, seawater and extinguishing water (wet, wet/dry or dry). It is also suitable for chemicals and technical liquids, compressed air (oil purity class 0–3), inert gases such as nitrogen and in negative pressure. FlowFit is suitable for a variety of applications, including technical building systems,
category: Pipe, Valves and Fittings/Plastic Pipe Fittings/Pressure Pipe Fittings/Tees/Tees.csv -> Geberit FlowFit 620.080.00.1 Equal tee 16mm
